  "chapter": {
    "number": 27,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Jotham Reigns in Judah"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          "Jotham was twenty-five years old when he became king, and he reigned in Jerusalem sixteen years. His motherâ€™s name was Jerushah",
          {
            "noteId": 760
          },
          "daughter of Zadok."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          "And he did what was right in the eyes of the LORD, just as his father Uzziah",
          {
            "noteId": 761
          },
          "had done. In addition, he did not enter the temple of the LORD. But the people still behaved corruptly."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          "Jotham rebuilt the Upper Gate of the house of the LORD, and he worked extensively on the wall at the hill of Ophel."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          "He also built cities in the hill country of Judah and fortresses and towers in the forests."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          "Jotham waged war against the king of the Ammonites and defeated them, and that year they gave him a hundred talents of silver,",
          {
            "noteId": 762
          },
          "ten thousand cors of wheat,",
          {
            "noteId": 763
          },
          "and ten thousand cors of barley.",
          {
            "noteId": 764
          },
          "They paid him the same in the second and third years."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          "So Jotham grew powerful because he ordered his ways before the LORD his God."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          "As for the rest of the acts of Jotham, along with all his wars and his ways, they are indeed written in the Book of the Kings of Israel and Judah."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          "He was twenty-five years old when he became king, and he reigned in Jerusalem sixteen years."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          "And Jotham rested with his fathers and was buried in the City of David. And his son Ahaz reigned in his place."
        ]
      }
    ],
